commit.message:
Use v.begin() for vectors instead of ADL begin(v) (#230)

No functional change (since `begin(x)` on a `std::vector` will
always find `std::begin` which dispatches back to `x.begin()`
anyway). But member name lookup is a lot cheaper, more idiomatic,
and also avoids the arcane problem reported in #197.

Also use `v.end() - 1` instead of `prev(end(v))`.

Fixes #197.

commit.message:
Eliminate `throw()`; use C++11 `noexcept` (#229)

This header already uses `nullptr` and `Args&&...`, plus
the `#error` directive on line 519 that forces C++11.
So it should be safe to use the `noexcept` keyword too.

Also, Rule-of-Zero the Error class, to avoid triggering
Clang's `-Wdeprecated-copy-with-dtor`.
